      "span_text": "Liaw, Liang and Wang (2007:107) note that \"virtual work means that employees do not need to physically go to corporate headquarters to work, but instead perform their professional jobs through Internet connection from remote home, car, hotel, satellite office, or other places different from the traditional central office.\" [CITATION_1] Golden ( :1642 confirms that telework, or working from home, is a form of virtual work also known as telecommuting.",
